",["$r","li",null,{"children":["A component ",["$r","em",null,{"children":"unmounts"}]," when it’s removed from the screen."]}],"
"]}],"
",["$r","p",null,{"children":[["$r","strong",null,{"children":["It’s a good way to think about components, but ",["$r","em",null,{"children":"not"}]," about Effects."]}]," Instead, try to think about each Effect independently from your component’s lifecycle. An Effect describes how to ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"/learn/synchronizing-with-effects","children":"synchronize an external system"}]," to the current props and state. As your code changes, synchronization will need to happen more or less often."]}],"
",["$r","p",null,{"children":"To illustrate this point, consider this Effect connecting your component to a chat server:"}],"
