",["$r","p",null,{"children":["The main reason your Effect will re-synchronize in practice is if some data it uses has changed. In the sandbox above, change the selected chat room. Notice how, when the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"roomId"}]," changes, your Effect re-synchronizes."]}],"
",["$r","p",null,{"children":["However, there are also more unusual cases in which re-synchronization is necessary. For example, try editing the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"serverUrl"}]," in the sandbox above while the chat is open. Notice how the Effect re-synchronizes in response to your edits to the code. In the future, React may add more features that rely on re-synchronization."]}],"
