",["$r","p",null,{"children":"Every time after your component re-renders, React will look at the array of dependencies that you have passed. If any of the values in the array is different from the value at the same spot that you passed during the previous render, React will re-synchronize your Effect."}],"
",["$r","p",null,{"children":["For example, if you passed ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"["general"]"}]," during the initial render, and later you passed ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"["travel"]"}]," during the next render, React will compare ",["$r","code",null,{"children":""general""}]," and ",["$r","code",null,{"children":""travel""}],". These are different values (compared with ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/is","target":"_blank","rel":"nofollow noopener noreferrer","children":["$r","code",null,{"children":"Object.is"}]}],"), so React will re-synchronize your Effect. On the other hand, if your component re-renders but ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"roomId"}]," has not changed, your Effect will remain connected to the same room."]}],"
