",["$r","p",null,{"children":["In the above example, deleting one Effect wouldn’t break the other Effect’s logic. This is a good indication that they synchronize different things, and so it made sense to split them up. On the other hand, if you split up a cohesive piece of logic into separate Effects, the code may look “cleaner” but will be ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect#chains-of-computations","children":"more difficult to maintain."}]," This is why you should think whether the processes are same or separate, not whether the code looks cleaner."]}],"
